        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I spent 4 hours and solo'ed the Coldain Military Wristguard quest this past weekend.  I had to create a warrior mule because I'm Kos in Kael, but it all went very smoothly.  I have now found that when soloing with pet, the only spell I need to recast is fear...darkness always lasts the entirety of the fight now.</P><P>Some nice things about the Coldain Wristguard that I was surprised by:<BR>It works with Bond of Death (I haven't parsed any logs to see if it actually does more damage, but it does "glow" or "flash" or whatever it's message is)</P><P>Also, my Amulet of Insight (extended enchancment III) item also flashes with BoD. Can anyone confirm if:<BR>1)  The EE3 effects actually does allow you to heal more from BoD<BR>2)  The EA3 effects actually does do more damage to mob from BoD</P><P>Sidenote:  lately, I have been trying to gain as many Focus Effect 3 items that I can.  Besides the Wristguard and the Amulet, I also have acquired an Iksar Hide Cap (7int 25hp and Reagent Conservation 3).  I have to say how much of a difference these level 3 focus effect items are making.  I'm saving lots of money in Peridots, Coffins, and bone chips (though I haven't confirmed Essence Emerald conservation yet (has anyone else?)).  Yeah, I know the bonechips don't mean much, but think of it this way, if you're down to one or no bone chips, and you can't get more quickly, you may be able to chain cast until the RC3 item flashes and you get a pet?  I don't konw if that would work, but it's something to try.</P><P>Saw a Gem Encrusted Ring AE3 item for sale in bazaar for 72kpp...too rich for me.</P><P>Hayzeus</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=322851" target="_blank"><img src="http://www3.telus.net/hayzeus/SnowBunny4.jpg " border=0></a></font></td>

