        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         No you dont need both items.  VC/BoD/Vex is now seen by EQ as two separate spells when you cast it.  One spell lands on mob .. the dmg portion.  One spell lands on you .. the heal portion.  If you only have EA III the dmg lasts longer.  Your heal portion will wear of in 54 seconds, but the dmg portion will last 66.</P><P> EA III for the dmg<BR> EE III for the healing</P><P>You can get EE III on quite a few items, but I get mine from Rokyl's</P><P>Rokyl's Channeling Crystal AC 10 +50 HP +50 MANA Effect: Extended Enhancement III</P><P><b><font color=blue>Retrievil Hesevil</font id=blue></b><BR><font color=red><b>58 DE Necromancer - Tallon Zek</font id=red></b><BR><font color=blue><b>56 Iksar Necromancer - Rodcet Nife</b></font id=blue><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=333155" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=333155</a></P><P>Edited by - Retrievil on 09/26/2002  14:54:31<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

